<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-590-057  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 590 057.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Nov 12 1990 v7 n45 p77(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Flagstaff's paperTamer to support NetWare. (network-aware versionof document storage and retreival system) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Higgins, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Flagstaff Engineering Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   paperTamer (Search software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Document Management SystemsProduct IntroductionSoftware packagesLocal Area Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Steve HigginsandM;In a bid to attract larger corporate customers, Flagstaff Engineering Inc. isendowing its PC-based paperTamer document storage and retrieval system withnetwork compatibility and the ability to work with several types of storagesystems.andM;paperTamer Network, due in January, will let users retrieve documents bytitle from any workstation on a Novell NetWare LAN, scan existing documentsfrom a properly equipped PC, and upgrade to multiple disk storage media asnecessary, said Laureen Simpson, product manager of office-automation systemsat Flagstaff.andM;The addition of network compatibility and the new storage media option in thenew network version will address weaknesses of Flagstaff's existingpaperTamer Professional and Personal Edition storage and retrieval programs,while retaining the simplicity that made the products useful, users said.andM;''paperTamer is an idiot-proof system for people not used to computers,''said Marty Stewart, president of Industrial Electrical Services Inc., asystems integrator in Montgomery, Ala.andP;  ''Drawbacks were that you couldn'tstore to more than one drive, and you couldn't use it on a network.''andM;Industrial Electrical Services has installed paperTamer at a large Montgomerymanufacturing firm that uses the system to store engineering documents.andP;  Bybringing paperTamer to the factory floor, the firm was able to do away withbulky paper files, according to Stewart.andM;The program, which allows users to search for a drawing by name and print acopy of it, also enabled the manufacturer to cut down on lost documents--acommon problem caused by employees checking out paper files, Stewart said.andM;paperTamer's new storage media options, which let users change from a singleCD ROM storage system to a multiple CD jukebox, will provide a growth pathfor the system's users, officials said.andM;paperTamer Network can be used with single or multiple optical drives fromvendors such as Hewlett-Packard Co., Mitsubishi Electronics America Inc. andPanasonic Industrial Co.andM;paperTamer Network software will cost $29,995 per server.andP;  New versions ofpaperTamer Professional and paperTamer Personal Edition that let usersupgrade to jukebox systems are now available for $195 and $795, respectively.andM;The products can be purchased through Flagstaff resellers or directly fromthe company.andM;Phoenix-based Flagstaff Engineering can be reached at (602) 779-3341.andO;</TEXT></DOC>